would it be possible to combine forest plot from meta package with
Prediction Distribution from metafor ?

Meta gives sort of more pleasing appearance in a quicker way but Prediction
Intervals are displayed in a form of red bar. On the other hand
metafor offers: predstyle: character string to specify the style of the
prediction interval (either "line" (the default), "polygon", "bar",
"shade", or "dist".

I especially like "dist" option that gives small distributional plots. Is
it possible to combine these two worlds together ? If yes I would be
